Vice President Mike Pence visited Tendon Manufacturing in Cleveland, Ohio, where he listened to business owners and employees discuss the burdens of Obamacare. Participants expressed concerns about the administrative paperwork and costs associated with the healthcare law. They also mentioned rising premiums, high deductibles, and limited coverage options. Pence emphasized the need to repeal and replace Obamacare to provide relief to American businesses and individuals. He highlighted the importance of giving states more flexibility in providing healthcare and increasing choices for consumers. The Vice President assured the participants that the administration is committed to lowering healthcare costs and improving the system.